.TH "rpcrdma_xprt_disconnect" 9 "rpcrdma_xprt_disconnect" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
rpcrdma_xprt_disconnect \- Disconnect underlying transport
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" rpcrdma_xprt_disconnect
.BI "(struct rpcrdma_xprt *r_xprt "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "r_xprt" 12
controlling transport instance
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Caller serializes. Either the transport send lock is held,
or we're being called to destroy the transport.

On return, \fIr_xprt\fP is completely divested of all hardware
resources and prepared for the next ->connect operation.
